title.narrative: Capacities of Child protection actors and services providers strengthened to better protect vulnerable children from abuse, violence and exploitation

description.narrative: 2019 was a transition year from humanitarian response to early recovery, and enhancing national capacities was one of child protection most significant areas of interventions. UNICEF continued to build national capacity to implement an effective CP case management system and to reinforce the capacity of service providers focusing on providing community-based interventions including quality psychosocial support, expansion of case management practices, the promotion of awareness raising initiatives on child protection including mine risk education. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:19/01/2020
